{{DISPLAYTITLE:Plat_DownByValue}}
{{Special|63|tag, speed, delay, height|Platform|DownByValue}}
* ''tag'': Tag of affected sector, or 0 to use the line's back sector.
* ''speed'': Platform's [[Definitions#Sector_movement_speed|movement speed]].  Doom's standard platforms move at 32, and blazing platforms move at 64.
* ''delay'': [[Definitions#Units_of_time|Tics]] before going back up.  Doom's platforms wait 105 tics.
* ''height'': Distance to lower, divided by 8.

Lowers a platform by (''height'' * 8) units, waits, and then raises it back to its original position. If ''tag'' is 0, then the sector on the line's back side is used.

